                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "A despondaemon can intuitively read the emotions of those it senses with its blindsense, knowing what emotion the target is experiencing at any given moment. They use this ability to isolate victims suffering from depression, their favorite prey.",
                "name": "Emotional Empathy",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "A despondaemon wages emotional warfare on creatures trapped inside it, convincing its victims of the futility of escape. A creature swallowed by the despondaemon\u2019s swallow whole ability must attempt a DC 16 Will save at the beginning of that creature\u2019s turn. On a failure, the creature is overwhelmed by negative emotions and is stunned for 1 turn.",
                "name": "Psychic Warfare",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "As a swift action, a despondaemon can harden its exterior, granting it a +2 circumstance bonus to AC but halving its speed. The daemon can end this effect with a swift action.",
                "name": "Harden Exterior",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su"
            }
